Message: 1
Date: Mon, 06 Jan 2003 13:15:31 -0500
From: Marshall Booth <mbooth+@pitt.edu>
Organization: University of Pittsburgh School of Medicine
To: "Mailshell User" <nospam@mailshell.com>
Subject: Re: [Mercedes] W-124 Door Checks

Gary, I have tried repairing/lubricating 201/124 door checks and only
succeded in making them work reliably again ONCE. I used LOTS of
AreoKroil on that one occasion and that has been the only lubricant that
ever resulted in an improvement that lasted more that a day or two. Now,
more than a year later that check is starting to get noisy again. The
use of AreoKroil seems almost counterintuitive (it's a very "thin"
penetrating oil used to loosen "frozen" nuts/bolts), but IT worked and
NOTHING else ever has worked! I expect that application of oil/grease to
a check that has been removed from the door SHOULD do a better job. If
you have a check failing in only a few years, that suggests that LOTS of
water/sluch/salt is getting inside the door. That should be addressed.

New door checks cost less the $20.

Marshall  
