Michelin is at it again, with 540 and 560 diameters (roughly 21.25 and 22
inches), with the PAX system. The new BMW Rolls Royce Phantom uses
265x790R540A tires. Also some Mazda, Renault, and Toyota concept vehicles at
this weeks US auto shows with 225x750R540A, 225x690R540A, 240x800R560A, and
215x730R560 tire sizes.

I vaguely remember the TRX coming in just two sizes. I wonder what
replacement rubber is still available to fit those wheels? Probably
unimportant, since it was a coupla Ford products using them, and all those
cars would have fallen completely apart by now.

Leave it to those French to think they can come up with a better tire and
wheel "system" by using something other than plain inches. ;-)

