Message: 10
From: "Eurowerks" <eurowerks@qx.net>
To: "Mailshell User" <nospam@mailshell.com>
   <mercedes@mercedesmailinglist.com>
Subject: Re: [Mercedes] OE W114 tires OE size (I measured)
Date: Mon, 6 Jan 2003 14:57:07 -0500

I disagree.  I just so happen to have an original set of wheels/tires (yes,
they are the original tires, never replaced) in that back of my shop.  I
just took a few measurements and came up with the following.  175 as we all
hopefully know is the width of the tire at its widest point in millimeters.
The next number you normally see is the aspect ratio, which is a percentage
of height versus width, which is missing from the original tires and then
the rim diameter being the last measurement.  The measurement that I just
came up with was 130 mm in sidewall height, measured from the tallest part
of the tire all the way down to the bottom of the bead.  If you do that
math, you will see that the OE sized tire is actually almost a 75 series
tire. (a little more than 74 percent as high as wide)  Therefore, without
hesitation I state as fact that the OE tire size on that car would be a
175/75/14.  Keep in mind that the wider you go regardless of whether or not
the aspect ratio stays the same percentage, the tire is getting taller.  I
personally use (on one of my 1975 model 240D's)a 185/70/14 without any
rubbing or problems.
Good luck!

Kirk A. Gilchrist
EURO-WERKS / Mercedes-Benz, BMW, Volvo Service and Repair
8 South Highland St. / Winchester, KY 40391 / 859-745-0125
eurowerks@qx.net / 888-522-0271 toll free



