There's an onramp near where I work where there are two lanes leading past
a set of metering lights.  The lanes then merge into a single onramp.

The other night, after the metering lights were off, a fellow in a pickup
truck saw fit to pass me in the left metering lane, because he didn't like
the slow speed with which I had approached the beginning of the onramp.  
(The road approaching the ramp is full of ruts.)  Of course, I was
beginning to accelerate to 60 to merge onto the highway

Immediately after he pulled ahead of me in the left metering lane, he
momentarily jammed the parking brake (sparks flying from under the truck)  
to slide the rear end sideways into my front bumper.

Lucky for him I left my weapons at home.

If you don't mind losing some of your windshield washer, you could load
the reservoir with something sticky and/or caustic and aim the nozzles
over the roof.

Justin
1987 300D Turbo 212k

